cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "BMSSP in Isabelle/HOL: an unconditional, non-vacuous size-parametric runtime bound"
abstract: >-
  A machine-checked Isabelle/HOL development of the Bounded Multi-Source Shortest Path
  (BMSSP) recurrence, culminating in an assumption-free, non-vacuous, size-parametric
  running-time theorem: the charged running time on an unbounded unit-weight directed
  path family is O(|V| * (ln |V|)^(2/3)) in the genuine graph size, with no hypotheses.
  The development contains no sorry, oops, or axiomatization and is verified by a clean
  Isabelle build (proofs and document). The final non-vacuous headline was developed with
  autonomous proof engineering via the GitHub Copilot CLI (Claude Opus 4.8).
type: software
